\begin_layout Chapter
Mathematical Expressions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Of course OpenPPL supports arbitary complex mathematical expressions.
 As as example let us consider odds and outs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset listings
inline false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

// Calling according to odds and outs
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

WHEN (AmountToCall / (AmountToCall + PotSize) > Outs / CardsLeft) CALL FORCE
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Off course this example is a bit simplistic.
 It does not consider other players in the pot, implied odds on future streets,
 the chance to semi-bluff, etc.
 But I think you get the point.
\end_layout

